@node INTRO "PopPhone/What is PopPhone?"

  What is PopPhone?
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  PopPhone is a program to help you keep track of names, addresses, E-mail
  accounts and telephone numbers.

  Not much more to say about this program, really - it's all very simple.
  Play around with it and you'll find out how it works. You can customize
  PopPhone to suit your own taste by using @{" tool types " link TTYPES}.

  PopPhone features Online AmigaGuide help, so just press <HELP> and you'll
  get help on the window currently active - try it!

  It's probably not the most advanced program in it's field - but it isn't
  supposed to be. It's just a small program doing what it does, without
  having a 1000 features. It works for me :)

  If you use the program please tell me about it! It's nice getting mail
  from users :)

  PS: Sorry for the dull icon... I'm a programmer, not an artist :-)
      If you make a nice icon for PopPhone, please send it to me, and I
      will include it in the next version. You will of course be
      credited!
      
@endnode

@node REQ "PopPhone/Requirements"

  Requirements
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~
  You'll need KickStart 2.0 or better and @{" MUI " link MUI} v2.3 installed. If you want the
  program to be able dial the phone numbers for you, you'll also need a
  modem :-)
  
  To utilize the localization feature, you must have KS2.1 or better.
@endnode

@node MUI "PopPhone/MUI"

  MUI - Magic User Interface
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  PopPhone uses MUI to create the graphical user interface (GUI). Use the
  MUI-prefs program to set things up the way you want it. You can specify
  the hotkey for PopPhone there too.. Check it out..
  
  MUI is available on Aminet and probably many other places. Get the
  package called something like @{b}mui23usr.lha@{ub}. 
@endnode

@node TTYPES "PopPhone/Tool Types"

  You can configure PopPhone by using the tool types descriped below.
  You cannot configure anything if you start PopPhone from a shell,
  so I suggest you always start it from Workbench :)

  Each of these tool types are optional. PopPhone can run fine without
  any of them used.


  Tool Types
  ~~~~~~~~~~
    @{b}TITLE=YES@{ub}
      Puts a title in the listview (name,city,telephone)

    @{b}TITLEATTR=BOLD|ITALICS|UNDERLINE@{ub}
      You can specify the text attributes of the lisview title. It's okay
      to mix the attributes. Ie. you can have the title in italics AND bold or
      just in bold etc.. If you don't specify TITLEATTR the title will be
      in plain text.

    @{b}NAMESPACE=<n>@{ub}
      Space in pixels between "Name" and "City" in listview title

    @{b}CITYSPACE=<n>@{ub}
      Space in pixels between "City" and "Telephone" in listview title

    @{b}DOUBLECLICK=EDIT|DIAL|NOACTION@{ub}
      Defines what happens when you doubleclick on an entry in the listview:

        À EDIT:     Opens the edit-window (if not already open)
        À DIAL:     Dials the phone number
        À NOACTION: Nothing happens! :-)

    @{b}DEVICE=<device>@{ub}
      Defines which device PopPhone uses when dialing via the modem.
      Default is "serial.device"

    @{b}DEVUNIT=<n>@{ub}
      Unit number on the device chosen. Default is 0.

    @{b}HANGUP=<n>@{ub}
      Defines how long PopPhone waits before sending an ATH to the modem,
      when dialing a phone number. The time is in 1/50 secs. Default is 200.
      (Corresspond to 4 seconds)

    @{b}PANEL=YES|NO@{ub}
      Hides the control buttons below the listview gadget.
      Default is YES (Buttons visible)

    @{b}LOG=YES|NO@{ub}
      Logs calls. Default is NO

    @{b}DIALHOTKEY=<hotkey>@{ub}
      Defines a special hotkey that, when pressed, will do exactly the same
      as if you pressed the Dial-button. This one is handy if you're
      running with no control panel, and then want to phone somebody.

      The hotkey string is in "commodity hotkey" format. You can read more
      about this in your Workbench User's guide. PopPhone allows a string
      of up to 30 characters.

    @{b}LOGFILE=<filename>@{ub}
      Defines the location and name of the logfile. The default filename is..
        
        PROGDIR:PopPhone.log

      ..which will put the logfile in the same place as the PopPhone
      executable. The filename can be up to 50 characters.
      

@endnode

