@node WIN_MAIN "PopPhone/Main window"

  Main window
  ~~~~~~~~~~~
  This window is where you'll be spending most of your time :-) The buttons
  at the bottom of the window more or less explains themselves, but here
  we go anyway:

     @{b}New@{ub}     À Opens the @{" Edit window " link WIN_EDIT}. Use this one
               to create a new entry in the phonebook.

     @{b}Edit@{ub}    À Edits the currently selected entry, and opens the @{" Edit window " link WIN_EDIT}
               If the phonebook is empty, nothing happens.

     @{b}Delete@{ub}  À Deletes the currently selected entry. You cannot undo this
               operation, so be careful.

     @{b}Toggle@{ub}  À In the @{" Edit window " link WIN_EDIT} you can specify two
               telephone numbers. Only one of these are displayed in the
               listview gadget. This button will toggle between the two
               sets.

     @{b}Manual Dial@{ub} À Opens a window where you can enter a phone number to dial

     @{b}Dial@{ub}    À Dials the telephone number of the currently selected entry.
               Use the toggle button to change between #1 and #2.

  The layout and other things can be configured by @{" tool types " link TTYPES}.

  All of these buttons can be hidden by using the @{b}Control Panel@{ub} feature 
  in the @{" Setup menu " link MENU}

@endnode

@node WIN_DIAL "PopPhone/Manual Dial window"

  Manual Dial window
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Here you can enter a phone number manually. When you press <RETURN> PopPhone will dial
  the entered number. Note: The Dial-button in the main window has nothing to do with
  this number.

@endnode

@node WIN_EDIT "PopPhone/Edit window"

  Edit window
  ~~~~~~~~~~~
  This window is used for creating a new entry, or editing an existing one.
  Take a look at the window's titlebar to see which "mode" you're in.

  You can use TAB and SHIFT-TAB to move between the different fields. Pressing
  <RETURN> will move to the next field.

  Press the @{b}OKAY@{ub} button to store the entry, or @{b}CANCEL@{ub} to discard it.
  If you have made changes and don't press the @{b}OKAY@{ub} button but instead
  selects another entry in the main window, your changes will be lost!

  The entry is inserted alphabetically in the phonebook. (Sorted by name)

  This window can be open together with the main window. When you select a
  new entry in the main window, the edit window will be updated.

  Closing the window by hitting the close gadget has the same effect
  as hitting the @{b}CANCEL@{ub} button.
@endnode

@node MENU "PopPhone/Menu"

  Project Menu
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~
    Save      À Saves the phone book to disk. The saved file is
                placed in the same directory where PopPhone itself
                is located.

                The file is called @{b}PopPhone.data@{ub}. It's in
                plain ASCII format.

    Copy      À The selected entry's name, address, zip code and
                city fields are copied to the clipboard. This makes
                it easy to grab names and addresses from PopPhone and
                using it in ex. a wordprocessor.

    Help...   À Opens the help system. You can still operate PopPhone
                while the help window is open.

    Iconify   À Closes all PopPhone's windows and places an appicon
                on the Workbench screen. Double click this icon to
                get PopPhone going again.

    About...  À Displays some information about PopPhone. Version number,
                author info and how much memory the phone book uses.

    Quit...   À Quits PopPhone. If you have made any changes to the
                phone book, you'll get a chance to save them.


  Print Menu
  ~~~~~~~~~~
    Selected  À Prints the currently selected entry.
    
    All       À Prints all entries in the phonebook.


  Setup Menu
  ~~~~~~~~~~
    Control Panel  À Hides and unhides the buttons below the listview
                     This can also be controled by @{" Tool Types " link TTYPES}
    
    Log            À Logs calls. When you make a call it will be registered
                     in the specified @{" log file " link TTYPES}

    MUI            À Launches the MUI-prefs program so you can change PopPhone's GUI.
                     (Only available if you're running MUI v3.1)

@endnode

@node HISTORY "PopPhone/Program history"

 Program history - a description of each release. Note: I use
 C='s definition of version numbers. Ex. 1.10 is newer than 1.5!

 (Newest on top)

 v2.2
 ~~~~
   Print option

   MUI-prefs can be launched from Settings-menu

   German locale and docs

   French locale

   Bug Fix: If you started with "Control Panel" on the menu wasn't updated

   Installer script


 v2.0
 ~~~~
   Control buttons can now be hidden if you want it.

   Fixed bug when dialing long phone numbers
   
   Log mode. Calls can be logged. Tooltype available to specify filename

   Tooltype to specify special dial hotkey

   Serial device wasn't closed if the modem didn't answer

   When device failed to open, PopPhone always said "Can't open serial.device",
   even when you used a different device.


 v1.70
 ~~~~~
   Clipboard support


 v1.40
 ~~~~~
   Changed layout of catalog files to work better with the new
   version of MUI.
   
   Used some new MUI-macros which saved some bytes off the executable
 

 v1.35
 ~~~~~
   MSG_WINEDIT_FAX added in catalogs (was hardcoded earlier)
   
   Nicer layout in edit-window


 v1.31
 ~~~~~
   Pops up with an error-requester if attempting to dial and modem
   isn't ready. Made an extra entry in the catalog to deal with this!


 v1.3
 ~~~~
   Pops up a requester if MUI v2.2 isn't installed on your system,
   instead of exiting quietly


 v1.2 
 ~~~~
   Fixed crash-problems when starting PopPhone without MUI installed

   Fixed crash-problems when starting PopPhone without locale.library
   installed

   Removed unused menu-items

   Added "Help..." item in menu


 v1.1
 ~~~~
   Put "..." on "New" and "Edit" buttons.

   Made the iconify hotkey easier to "reach" :)


 v1.0
 ~~~~
   First release

@endnode

